Acting on a tip-off officers arrested the woman in an undercover operation in Lansdowne yesterday. CAPE TOWN - A Kenilworth woman has been arrested for allegedly hiring an employee to kill her husband. Acting on a tip-off officers arrested the woman in an undercover operation in Lansdowne yesterday. It's alleged the woman offered a staffer R 200,000 to murder her spouse. The police's Frederick van Wyk says: "A sting operation was conducted in the parking area of the Lansdowne railway station where a women handed over an undisclosed amount of cash to have her husband assassinated. The 34-year-old woman was arrested shortly thereafter and is due to appear in the Wynberg Magistrate's Court tomorrow on a charge of conspiracy to commit murder."